Help me build real intuition for [X]. Do it in this order:

1. The general idea of what it is.
2. The motivating problem and rigorous historical development of the idea.
3. Give me worked examples from different fields, then explicitly compare them — what's structurally identical underneath the different surface dressing?
4. For each required condition/hypothesis, give me near-misses: a case that's identical to a valid one except that single condition is broken, so I see exactly what that condition was buying us.
5. Its place in the family: what it generalizes, what it's a special case of, its most commonly confused sibling.
6. Give me new, unlabeled problems so we can try to identify whether this idea applies.
7. Deliberately tricky negative cases at the end — looks eligible, isn't.

(concerning Q4 and Q6, give me a few questions of increasing difficulty and lack of intuitiveness/obviousness to force me to intuit on how the theorem is the key to solving.)


You must write thoroughly on each of these numbered points
